name: Neuroanatomy
description: This is a rigorous, introductory course that presents the functional and comparative anatomy of the vertebrate brain. It is designed for students who intend to continue with studies in the Neurosciences and related areas.
prerequisites: 9 FCE complete, PSL300H1, HMB200H1/HMB220H1/PSY290H1, BIO230H1/ BIO255H1
